Sentencas: Ceria-samaria compositions were prepared by freeze-drying, yielding very homogeneous and fluorite single phase powders at temperatures as low as 375 degrees C. These powders were used to obtain dense ceramics by sintering at 1600 degrees C for 10 h. The mixed transport properties of these materials were characterized by impedance spectroscopy and the Hebb-Wagner ion-blocking method, at temperatures in the range 700-950 degrees C.
Titulo: Mixed transport properties of Ce1-xSmxO2-x/2 system under fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: The onset of n-type electronic conductivity was expressed as a function of oxygen partial pressure and temperature, and was found dependent on the Sm-content.
Titulo: Mixed transport properties of Ce1-xSmxO2-x/2 system under fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: Mixed transport properties were also analyzed for conditions in which the samples are exposed to fuels in a SOFC, either as electrolyte or component of cermet anodes.
Titulo: Mixed transport properties of Ce1-xSmxO2-x/2 system under fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: The degree of fuel conversion and corresponding changes in gas composition produce changes in the mixed transport properties of SOFC electrolytes, with emphasis on the fuel side.
Titulo: Mixed transport properties of Ce1-xSmxO2-x/2 system under fuel cell operating conditions

Sentencas: The mixed transport properties were also used to estimate open cell voltage as a function of fuel conversion.
Titulo: Mixed transport properties of Ce1-xSmxO2-x/2 system under fuel cell operating conditions
